The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 October is 91,451 (10,540.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 October, there were 4,671 new confirmed cases (538.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 October, there were 3,578 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 31% (1,093 extra cases).
